Abstract    :
              0125413 McGruder  This award supports a planning visit to South Africa in
              August 2001 for Professor Charles McGruder, Department of Physics and
              Astronomy, Western Kentucky University, Bowling Green, KY.  Professor McGruder,
              who is the President of the National Society of Black Physicists, will meet
              with leading South African scientists to formulate joint research projects
              between graduate students in the United States and South Africa.  He will also
              meet with Patricia Whitelock, Deputy Director of the South African Astronomical
              Observatory, to discuss a planned graduate course in basic space science to
              attract students from all over Africa. 
